public interface TreeNode<T extends TreeNode<T>>

Represents a DTO that is a node in a tree. This node has a single parent, any number of children, and a human-readable description. The use of "T extends TreeNode" on this class implies that the child nodes from getChildren() and setChildren() are assignable from the same generic type (T) as the parent.
